                            <comment id="15727778" author="stack" created="Wed, 7 Dec 2016 05:39:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is what I&apos;ll commit. Adds a section on standalone.over.hdfs. Removes scary bit about local fs not supporting flush/sync &amp;#8211; fixed a good while ago.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15729001" author="jrottinghuis" created="Wed, 7 Dec 2016 15:22:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for clarifying and documenting this!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In conf/hbase-site you still have a value in hbase.rootdir that appears to point to an actual HDFS url. Did you mean to &quot;hdfs://namenode.example.org:9000/hbase&quot; as in the description of that property, or perhaps &quot;hdfs://namenode.example.org:8020/hbase&quot; as described in /src/main/asciidoc/_chapters/configuration.adoc ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15729064" author="stack" created="Wed, 7 Dec 2016 15:48:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jrottinghuis&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jrottinghuis&quot;&gt;Joep Rottinghuis&lt;/a&gt; Let me fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15729354" author="stack" created="Wed, 7 Dec 2016 17:37:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;More edits on quickstart section removing stale info and more removal of language that frightens folks away from use of standalone or local fs.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15729461" author="stack" created="Wed, 7 Dec 2016 18:18:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;.002 is what I pushed (site-build is 15minutes &amp;#8211; too long).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15729464" author="stack" created="Wed, 7 Dec 2016 18:19:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I pushed the last patch. Will update the site separately.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15730199" author="vrushalic" created="Wed, 7 Dec 2016 22:54:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you for the fix, Stack. This is very useful for us in Timeline Service in YARN. I am updating the documentation for Timeline Service to reflect this change in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/YARN-5980&quot; title=&quot;Update documentation for single node hbase deploy&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;YARN-5980&quot;&gt;YARN-5980&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
